---
title: Onion Crunch Chicken Includes recyclable aluminum tray
description: This hearty chicken dish is a breeze to put together, thanks to our oven-ready trays that keep cleanup to a minimum. You’ll top the chicken with honey Dijon dressing, melty Monterey Jack cheese, and a fried onion coating that crisps up to golden perfection as it bakes. Buttery baby potatoes and roasted green beans complete the meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/673b9b8afd3e9058428acbf0-5c4d5412.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/673b9b8afd3e9058428acbf0-en-US.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/prep-and-bake-onion-crunch-chicken-673b9b8afd3e9058428acbf0
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 44 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 420 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce (except potatoes).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}; place in center of #oven-ready aluminum tray{}.

Place @honey Dijon dressing{1%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}; reserve remaining @honey Dijon dressing{1/2%tbsp} in a separate small bowl for serving. Brush tops of each chicken cutlet with 1/2 TBSP dressing. Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Using your hands, finely crush @crispy fried onions{1%unit} in their package; sprinkle over cheese, pressing to adhere.

Arrange @green beans{6%ounce} around chicken in tray. Add a drizzle of @oil{} over green beans and season with half the @garlic powder{1/2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, arrange chicken in one tray and green beans in second tray.

Roast on middle rack until green beans are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When chicken has about 8 minutes left, place sealed @microwavable multicolor baby potatoes{12%ounce} bag, front side down, in the #microwave{}; microwave ~{5%minutes}. Let bag cool in microwave for ~{2%minutes}.

> TIP: You can also transfer potatoes to a medium microwave-safe bowl, cover tightly with plastic wrap, and microwave until tender, about 5 minutes.

Carefully open bag (watch out for steam!) and add remaining @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @butter{1%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Toss until potatoes are evenly coated.

Divide chicken, green beans, and potatoes between plates. Serve with reserved dressing on the side.